p.-text
  | Expansion panels are components designed to be folded and stacked in sequence. They have four states: active,
  | pending, done and disabled. When pending, which is the default state, only the title is shown. When active, panels expand to show
  | content or forms. When done, content or form data is presented in a read only state. When disabled, a muted title
  | is shown in a non-clickable state.

  .example.-mb3.-mt3
    .-p3
      chi-expansion-panel(step='1', heading='Done panel', state='done')
        div(slot='done' class='-text') 
          | CenturyLink
          br
          | 1100 112th Ave NE
          br
          | Suite 400
          br
          | Bellevue, WA 98004
        div(slot='change')
          button.a-btn.-brand.-flat Change
      chi-expansion-panel(step='2', heading='Active panel', state='active')
        div(slot='active') 
          h5.-mt--0 Active panel title
          p.-text.-mb--0 Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipisicing elit. At atque consequatur consequuntur excepturi
            |  illo maiores, nobis placeat recusandae rem! Accusantium ad in minus molestiae? Commodi cupiditate labore
            | nihil sed veritatis!
        div(slot='footer')
          button.a-btn.-lg.-primary Continue
      chi-expansion-panel(step='3', heading='Pending panel')
      chi-expansion-panel(step='4', heading='Disabled panel', state='disabled')
    ul#a-tabs.a-tabs.-ml--3
      li.-active
        a(href='#a-tabs-done') Done
      li
        a(href='#a-tabs-active') Active
      li
